{"title_page": "List of AFC Asian Cup hat-tricks", "text_new": "[[File:Hossein_Kalani_at_Shiroudi_Stadium.jpg|thumb|[[Hossein Kalani]] scored the first hat-trick in the tournament's history, in the ]]\nThis is a '''list of hat-tricks in the AFC Asian Cup''', that being when a player scores three or more goals in a tournament match of the [[AFC Asian Cup]] (not including [[AFC Asian Cup qualification|qualification]] matches). [[Hat-trick|Hat-tricks]] have occurred 18 times across the 17 editions.\n\nThe first tournament was held in [[1956 AFC Asian Cup|1956]], however no hat-tricks were scored in the first four competitions. The first instance was in [[1972 AFC Asian Cup|1972]], where [[Hossein Kalani]] scored three goals for [[Iran national football team|Iran]] against [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] in the group stage.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.insideworldfootball.com/asian-cup-1972/|title=Asian Cup 1972|website=Inside World Football|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> Later on in the same tournament again for Iran, [[Ali Jabbari]] scored three goals inside nine minutes to defeat [[Thailand national football team|Thailand]] 3\u20132. The first time a player would score four goals in a match would be [[1980 AFC Asian Cup|1980]], where [[Behtash Fariba]] achieved the feat in a 7\u20130 win for Iran over [[Bangladesh national football team|Bangladesh]]. After 1980, three tournaments went by without a hat-trick before [[Ali Daei]] scored four goals for Iran in a 6\u20132 win over [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] in [[1996 AFC Asian Cup|1996]], also marking the first time at least three goals were scored in a match in the knockout stage. Two tournaments later in [[2004 AFC Asian Cup|2004]], another knockout stage hat-trick was achieved by [[Ali Karimi]] for Iran in a 4\u20133 win against South Korea, again in the quarter-finals.\n\nIran have scored the most hat-tricks with six, while Bangladesh and [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] have conceded the most, with three each. No player has scored multiple hat-tricks in the Asian Cup. Also, every hat-trick scorer has had their side go on to win their match\n\n== Hat-tricks ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n! colspan=\"2\" |Key\n|-\n|<sup>4</sup>\n|Player scored four goals in the match\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Sequence\n!Player\n!Time of goals\n!Representing\n!Final score\n!Opponent\n!Tournament\n!Round\n!Date\n|-\n|{{nts|1}}.\n|{{sortname|Hossein|Kalani}}\n|34', 70', 78'\n|{{fb|IRN|1964}}\n|3\u20130\n|{{fb|IRQ|1963}}\n|[[1972 AFC Asian Cup|1972]]\n|Group stage\n|9 May 1972\n|-\n|{{nts|2}}.\n|{{sortname|Ali|Jabbari}}\n|80', 86', 88'\n|{{fb|IRN|1964}}\n|3\u20132\n|{{fb|THA}}\n|[[1972 AFC Asian Cup|1972]]\n|Group stage\n|13 May 1972\n|-\n|{{nts|3}}.\n|{{sortname|Gholam Hossein|Mazloumi}}\n|63', 74', 80'\n|{{fb|IRN|1964}}\n|8\u20130\n|{{fb|South Yemen}}\n|[[1976 AFC Asian Cup|1976]]\n|Group stage\n|8 June 1976\n|-\n|{{nts|4}}.\n|{{sortname|Behtash|Fariba}}<sup>4</sup>\n|11', 34', 80', 82'\n|{{fb|IRN}}\n|7\u20130\n|{{fb|BAN}}\n|[[1980 AFC Asian Cup|1980]]\n|Group stage\n|22 September 1980\n|-\n|{{nts|5}}.\n|{{sortname|Choi|Soon-Ho}}\n|26', 53', 78'([[Penalty kick (association football)|P]])\n|{{fb|KOR|1949}}\n|4\u20131\n|{{fb|UAE}}\n|[[1980 AFC Asian Cup|1980]]\n|Group stage\n|24 September 1980\n|-\n|{{nts|6}}.\n|{{sortname|Shen|Xiangfu}}\n|1', 5', 72'\n|{{fb|CHN}}\n|6\u20130\n|{{fb|BAN}}\n|[[1980 AFC Asian Cup|1980]]\n|Group stage\n|25 September 1980\n|-\n|{{nts|7}}.\n|{{sortname|Xu|Yonglai}}\n|16', 79', 89'\n|{{fb|CHN}}\n|6\u20130\n|{{fb|BAN}}\n|[[1980 AFC Asian Cup|1980]]\n|Group stage\n|25 September 1980\n|-\n|{{nts|8}}.\n|{{sortname|Ali|Daei}}<sup>4</sup>\n|66', 76', 83', 89'([[Penalty kick (association football)|P]])\n|{{fb|IRN}}\n|6\u20132\n|{{fb|KOR|1949}}\n|[[1996 AFC Asian Cup|1996]]\n|Quarter-finals\n|16 December 1996\n|-\n|{{nts|9}}.\n|{{sortname|Akinori|Nishizawa}}\n|14', 25', 49'\n|{{fb|JPN}}\n|8\u20131\n|{{fb|UZB}}\n|[[2000 AFC Asian Cup|2000]]\n|Group stage\n|17 October 2000\n|-\n|{{nts|10}}.\n|{{sortname|Naohiro|Takahara}}\n|18', 20', 57'\n|{{fb|JPN}}\n|8\u20131\n|{{fb|UZB}}\n|[[2000 AFC Asian Cup|2000]]\n|Group stage\n|17 October 2000\n|-\n|{{nts|11}}.\n|{{sortname|Lee|Dong-Gook}}\n|30', 76', 90+1'\n|{{fb|KOR}}\n|3\u20130\n|{{fb|INA}}\n|[[2000 AFC Asian Cup|2000]]\n|Group stage\n|19 October 2000\n|-\n|{{nts|12}}.\n|{{sortname|Mohammad|Al-Shalhoub}}\n|35', 78', 86'\n|{{fb|KSA}}\n|5\u20130\n|{{fb|UZB}}\n|[[2000 AFC Asian Cup|2000]]\n|Group stage\n|20 October 2000\n|-\n|{{nts|13}}.\n|{{sortname|Ali|Karimi}}\n|10', 20', 77'\n|{{fb|IRN}}\n|4\u20133\n|{{fb|KOR}}\n|[[2004 AFC Asian Cup|2004]]\n|Quarter-finals\n|31 July 2004\n|-\n|{{nts|14}}.\n|{{sortname|Ismail|Abdul-Latif}}<sup>4</sup>\n|16', 19', 35', 77'\n|{{fb|BHR}}\n|5\u20132\n|{{fb|IND}}\n|[[2011 AFC Asian Cup|2011]]\n|Group stage\n|14 January 2011\n|-\n|{{nts|15}}.\n|{{sortname|Shinji|Okazaki}}\n|8', 13', 80'\n|{{fb|JPN}}\n|5\u20130\n|{{fb|KSA}}\n|[[2011 AFC Asian Cup|2011]]\n|Group stage\n|17 January 2011\n|-\n|{{nts|16}}.\n|{{sortname|Hamza|Al-Dardour}}<sup>4</sup>\n|35', 45+2', 75', 80'\n|{{fb|JOR}}\n|5\u20131\n|{{fb|PLE}}\n|[[2015 AFC Asian Cup|2015]]\n|Group stage\n|16 January 2015\n|-\n|{{nts|17}}.\n|{{sortname|Almoez|Ali}}<sup>4</sup>\n|9', 11', 55', 60'\n|{{fb|QAT}}\n|6\u20130\n|{{fb|PRK}}\n|[[2019 AFC Asian Cup|2019]]\n|Group stage\n|13 January 2019\n|-\n|{{nts|18}}.\n|{{sortname|Vitalij|Lux}}\n|24', 51', 77'\n|{{fb|KGZ}}\n|3\u20131\n|{{fb|PHI}}\n|[[2019 AFC Asian Cup|2019]]\n|Group stage\n|16 January 2019\n|}\n\n=== By nation ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Nation\n!Hat-tricks for\n!Hat-tricks against\n|-\n|{{fb|IRN}}\n|6\n|0\n|-\n|{{fb|JPN}}\n|3\n|0\n|-\n|{{fb|KOR|1949}}\n|2\n|2\n|-\n|{{fb|CHN}}\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|{{fb|KSA}}\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|{{fb|BHR}}\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|{{fb|JOR}}\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|{{fb|QAT}}\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|{{fb|KGZ}}\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|{{fb|BAN}}\n|0\n|3\n|-\n|{{fb|UZB}}\n|0\n|3\n|-